Durban - Two suspects are due to appear in the  Umlazi Magistrate's Court on Wednesday for possession of unlicensed firearm, attempted murder and discharging a firearm in public. On Monday evening, Umlazi police officers were conducting crime prevention duties in V Section when they noticed two men discharging firearms in public. The suspects aged 36 and 38 spotted the police officers and a shootout ensued. "One suspect sustained a gunshot wound on the right thigh and the second suspect was found hiding in a nearby house," said police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala. "The injured suspect was taken to hospital under police guard while the second suspect was detained at Umlazi police station. "Two 38 special revolver with ammunition were recovered and will be subjected to ballistic testing to establish if they were used in any other crimes in the province." Police encouraged communities to report such criminal behaviour immediately to their local police and not to allow criminals to move freely in their neighbourhoods. Daily News